        <abstract>
            <p>Is glad of CD’s appointment and hopes it will be a source of happiness and honour.</p>
            <p>Answers a query about books.</p>
            <p>Suggests CD go to Geological Society, present himself, as AS’s friend, to William Lonsdale and study the Society’s collection.</p>
            <p>Tells CD of his work in Wales; includes a diagram and explanations.</p>
            <p>Ramsay’s death a grievous loss.</p>
        </abstract>
